msgctxt "Talk01"
msgid ""
"<1.se_co><2.so><3.re_co>The more I see of this place, the more\n"
"it hits me just how hard the old tragedy\n"
"struck here.<4.ra><5.so>But even knowing that, seeing so many\n"
"Guardians... It boggles the mind.<6.ra>That warrior must have been some "
"threat\n"
"to the forces of darkness, huh?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: set_colour (blue)
#. 5: reset_colour
msgctxt "Talk04"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Almost hard to believe they managed to\n"
"hold back a whole horde of Guardians\n"
"here.\n"
"If not for <2.se_co>Fort Hateno<3.re_co> and the warrior,\n"
"there'd be no such place as\n"
"<4.se_co>Hateno Village<5.re_co> anymore."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: raw
msgctxt "Talk06"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I'd love to keep jawing with you about\n"
"<2.se_co>Fort Hateno<3.re_co> and the warrior—don't get\n"
"me wrong.<4.ra>But I'm observing a moment of silence\n"
"for the warrior and his troops who fought\n"
"to the last against the Guardians.\n"
"We can pick it up again in the morning."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: raw
#. 3: pause (longer)
#. 4: sound
msgctxt "Talk08"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I used to think the old tragedy was\n"
"ancient history. Nothing to do with\n"
"my life.<2.ra>But when I stop to consider that my\n"
"life is only possible because of those\n"
"who fought tooth and nail for us...<3.pa>\n"
"<4.so>Well, I start to feel a tear in my eye.\n"
"Although that could also just be the rain."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: choice
msgctxt "Talk12"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hiya! My name's Garill. Come to see\n"
"<2.se_co>Fort Hateno<3.re_co>, I take it?<4.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: pause (longer)
#. 2: raw
#. 3: set_colour (blue)
#. 4: reset_colour
#. 5: pause (short)
#. 6: choice
msgctxt "Talk13"
msgid ""
"I wasn't sleeping...<1.pa> I wasn't!<2.ra>I was praying for the souls of "
"the warrior\n"
"and all who died here at <3.se_co>Fort Hateno<4.re_co>.<5.pa>\n"
"That's a totally different thing!\n"
"You're welcome to join me if you want.<6.ch>\n"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: raw
#. 3: sound
#. 4: set_colour (blue)
#. 5: reset_colour
msgctxt "Talk14"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Figured as much. It's well worth seeing!<2.ra><3.so><4.se_co>Fort "
"Hateno<5.re_co> here was the last line of\n"
"defense between Hateno Village and the\n"
"awful tragedy all those years ago.\n"
"Everyone's got to come and pay their\n"
"respects at least once in life, right?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: raw
#. 3: sound
#. 4: set_colour (blue)
#. 5: reset_colour
#. 6: pause (short)
#. 7: pause (short)
msgctxt "Talk15"
msgid ""
"<1.so>You come up to talk to me and then\n"
"give me the brush-off? What gives?<2.ra><3.so>Listen, <4.se_co>Fort "
"Hateno<5.re_co> here was the last line\n"
"of defense between Hateno Village and\n"
"the tragedy all those years ago.\n"
"You're a Hylian—you ought to know \n"
"these things!<6.pa> Have some respect!\n"
"<7.pa>Learn some history!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: pause (short)
msgctxt "Talk16"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I don't mean to pressure you. But\n"
"<2.se_co>Fort Hateno<3.re_co> here was the last line of\n"
"defense for Hateno all those years ago.\n"
"If not for this fort and the soldiers who\n"
"held the line here, Hateno Village as we\n"
"know it might be gone entirely.\n"
"I hang around to pray that those who\n"
"gave their lives find peace and to pass\n"
"on the story of the hero.\n"
"I owe that much to the soldiers who\n"
"fought so that we might live today!\n"
"<4.pa>I think everyone does."
msgstr ""

#. 1: raw
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "Talk17"
msgid ""
"That's a pretty enlightened thing to say\n"
"for such a young kid!<1.ra><2.se_co>Fort Hateno<3.re_co> here was the "
"last line of\n"
"defense between Hateno Village and the\n"
"terrible tragedy all those years ago.\n"
"If not for this fort and the soldiers who\n"
"held the line here, Hyrule as we know it\n"
"might be gone entirely.\n"
"It's our duty as the survivors to pray that\n"
"those who gave their lives find peace\n"
"and to pass on the story of the warrior."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: choice
msgctxt "Talk18"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Do you know the story of the warrior\n"
"who fought here at <2.se_co>Fort Hateno<3.re_co>?<4.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: raw
#. 3: pause (short)
#. 4: raw
#. 5: pause (short)
#. 6: pause (short)
msgctxt "Talk19"
msgid ""
"<1.so>So 100 years ago, we had these\n"
"special warriors called Champions.<2.ra>The warrior who fought here was\n"
"supposedly one of them.<3.pa> I heard the\n"
"others all died in the big fight.\n"
"The warrior, though... Some say he gave\n"
"his life here too.<4.ra>But others think he went into a deep\n"
"sleep to prepare to fight another day.<5.pa>\n"
"Which would mean he's still alive, right?\n"
"I wonder if I'll still be around when he\n"
"wakes up.<6.pa> I'd love to meet the guy."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: raw
#. 4: pause (short)
#. 5: pause (short)
msgctxt "Talk20"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Oh, that's excellent! <2.pa>Saves me the\n"
"trouble of having to tell you.<3.ra>You know, most people think the "
"warrior\n"
"gave his life here in battle with the\n"
"forces of darkness.\n"
"But some believe he actually went into a\n"
"deep sleep, so he could live again to\n"
"fight another day!\n"
"If that's true, he must still be alive.<4.pa>\n"
"I wonder if I'll still be around when he\n"
"wakes up...<5.pa> I'd love to meet the guy."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: raw
msgctxt "Talk21"
msgid ""
"<1.so>The warrior and his soldiers at\n"
"<2.se_co>Fort Hateno <3.re_co>risked their lives to\n"
"protect the world.<4.ra>I wasn't there at the time, but I'm alive\n"
"now because of them, and I've got to\n"
"make sure future generations know it!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Talk22"
msgid ""
"<1.so>If I'd been alive 100 years ago...I like\n"
"to think I'd have fought these Guardians\n"
"here, right at the warrior's side."
msgstr ""

